The paper discusses the challenges faced by an agile team working in a non-agile organization, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The focus on work motivation and the impact on team dynamics suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. The study also touches on the cultural and organizational aspects of the interface between the agile team and the non-agile organization, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study uses qualitative data analysis techniques, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of developing algorithms for analyzing qualitative data.
